    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Project Overview",
      "type": "text",
      "content": "## The Challenge\n\nTraditional month-end close processes were consuming 12+ days with manual reconciliation, reactive issue management, and high resource consumption. The finance team needed an intelligent solution to transform their close operations.\n\n### Key Pain Points:\n• 12+ day close cycles consuming 120+ hours of manual effort\n• Reactive management with issues discovered too late\n• Resource constraints with Controller and specialists overloaded\n• No real-time progress tracking or bottleneck identification\n• Error-prone manual reconciliation leading to variance detection delays\n\n### Business Impact Analysis:\n• **$165K Annual Labor Cost**: Senior Controller (40h/month × $95/h) + 2 Analysts (80h/month × $65/h) + overtime premiums\n• **$50K+ Risk Exposure**: Delayed issue identification leading to compliance risks\n• **Opportunity Cost**: Senior staff tied up in operational vs strategic work\n\n*Our solution eliminated these pain points through intelligent automation.*",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "solution",
      "title": "The ML-Powered Solution",
      "type": "text",
      "content": "## System Architecture\n\nBuilt an enterprise-grade ML-powered financial close automation system with three core components:\n\n### 🔧 **Advanced ML Reconciliation Engine**\n• Z-score anomaly detection with 2.5σ threshold\n• Predictive models achieving 87% accuracy in variance identification\n• Automated variance identification and flagging\n\n### 🤖 **Process Automation Framework**  \n• 17-task automated workflow including: journal entry validation, bank reconciliation, intercompany eliminations, and variance analysis\n• Exception handling for complex reconciliation scenarios\n• Real-time progress monitoring and bottleneck identification\n\n### 📊 **Predictive Analytics Engine**\n• SQLite database with normalized enterprise schema\n• Real-time KPI monitoring and executive dashboards\n• Automated reporting with detailed audit trails",
      "order": 2
    },
